** the vision is real
   as i got to bed im thinking about what we are working towards and i can feel it getting closer

   so we have a few pieces to put together but they promise to be very interesting:
   - {https://github.com/sst/opencode}[opencode] for the cli that we want to use
   - {https://github.com/ravitemer/mcphub.nvim}[mcphub] for neovim is going to be interesting because it lets us setup mcp servers
   - what servers will we be setting up? why {https://github.com/bigcodegen/mcp-neovim-server}[the neovim one] ofcourse!
   -- wouldnt be right if we didnt start working through the api so that we can control neovim while its still going on!

   What is even better than all of this, is the fact that it dovetails pefectly with the work we did in the systemd and fish config to allow us to start a server on a named pipe and connect a mcp server to it!

   so now we have atleast two things that we want to connect to:
   - neovide for gui
   - mcp for ai control!

   This gives a reason to the way that we are using this and allowing us to have neovim be the ultimate structured updating piece that allows us to set the ais off with a system that REALLY allows leverage

   and how will it know how to use all of the custom functionality? because we are able to have the whole literate config setup ofcourse! 

