   one of the reasons this template directory has been fucking with me is that the files need to be able to run EVEN IF WE ARENT USING THEM. this was what was messing with me was the fact that i passively opened the fennel file without actually make it so that we are able to edit the lua file

   This makes my solution MORE viable now because as i had hoped it actually steps around this problem and allows us to leverage the machine-to-machine differences WITHOUT dealing with this template bullshit so im going to say that I am doubling down on this approach when it comes to neovim since that makes sense for several reasons including the fact that we shouldnt need templates since we are actually going to be using this in a real programming language, we can just do all of these checks ourselves in fennel

   but more importantly, opencode and anthropic were absolutely no help, they were completely unable to diagnose the problem and it just goes to show that when we try to outsource our jobs to the machines we are going to hit some major barriers around getting the work done.

