* stuff to consider 2025-07-29
  so we just got done solving a problem with debugging an error in neorg itself so the whole thing broke for a minute..

This reminds us of the importance of this project to make the whole thing runnable from a linux machine made with `mkosi` this way we have what we need to achieve the speed necessary and get the next version of our config shipping WITHOUT breaking the whole thing lol

in addition, we should consider making neorg one of the first things that we go through and work on so that we are ready to have a conversation about what is necessary in the long run to get it all working and structured

  finally, we want to use conform with the injected formatter to allow us to format even when we are within another document, this will make it so that the main files arent such a pain to read.

  put these all together, and we should have a solid way to work through these separate pieces.

  the other integrations we want to turn on are otter.nvim for integration within the document so we can get lsp diagnostics without leaving the environment, as well as looking glass so that we can pop the little snippets out into their own file and work with it from there.

this will have a few beneficial qualities but not the least of which is the ability to just pop something out and make it so that we are able to format it without worrying about the injected formatter

